MolFC User License Agreement 
All MolFC requestors MUST agree to the following license agreement. 

With regard to the MolFC programs, with which you have supplied me a copy, I
agree to the following conditions:

1) I will not supply a copy of the code to anyone outside my institution or
   corporation for any reason whatsoever. Instead, I will refer any requests for
   copies of the program to you at the Theoretical Chemistry Group of the
   University of Salerno. This in no way limits my making of copies of the
   codefor backup purposes, or for running on more than one computer system at my
   institution or home.

2) I understand that copyright or ownership rights to MolFC are retained by
   the University of Salernoand contributors to the MolFC package. I will not
   incorporate any part of MolFC into any other program system, either for sale
   or for non-profit distribution, without written permission from the
   Theoretical Chemistry Group of the University of Salerno, 
   
3) I understand that MolFC cannot be considered to be bug free, and
   accordingly the Theoretical Chemistry Group of the University of Salerno
   supplies the MolFC software on an "as is" basis, with no additional
   responsibility or liability,

4) If results obtained with MolFC are published in the scientific literature,
   I will reference the program from the articles 
   Borrelli R., A. Peluso J. Chem.  Phys., 125, 194308 (2006).
   Borrelli R., Capobianco A., Peluso A., J. Phys. Chem. A, 116, 9934 (2012).
   Borrelli R., Capobianco A., Peluso A., Can. J. Chem., 91, 495 (2013).

5) This license is considered a "Research Group" license. Thus anyone directly
   associated with yourresearch group is covered by the license and may share
   your copy of MolFC on all of your group's computer resources.

